<span id="freeTextContainer16635922407791765841"><b>I&apos;ll Be Damned</b><br/><br/>How could the same F. Scott Fitzgerald who composed such a brilliant novel in <u>The Great Gatsby</u> have preceded it with such a lifeless moral tale?<br/><br/>A bantam-cock and his haughty hussy, Anthony and Gloria Patch, squander their days for more than a decade of their lives anticipating an inheritance of a large part of the estate of Anthony&apos;s grandfather, a Rockefeller-type magnate, who excludes them from his Last Will and Testament because of their debauched style of living. <br/><br/>It&apos;s just hard</span>
  <span id="freeText16635922407791765841" style="display:none"><b>I'll Be Damned</b><br /><br />How could the same F. Scott Fitzgerald who composed such a brilliant novel in <u>The Great Gatsby</u> have preceded it with such a lifeless moral tale?<br /><br />A bantam-cock and his haughty hussy, Anthony and Gloria Patch, squander their days for more than a decade of their lives anticipating an inheritance of a large part of the estate of Anthony's grandfather, a Rockefeller-type magnate, who excludes them from his Last Will and Testament because of their debauched style of living. <br /><br />It's just hard to be captivated by two despicable anti-heroes.<br /><br />The gritty sand before the pearl.</span>
